"{\"uid\": \"thesouthafrican.com-sport-paris-olympics-2024-what-time-wayde-van-niekerk-action-olympics-wednesday-night\", \"text\": \"Copyright Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd. All Rights Reserved.  thesouthafrican.com is a division of Blue Sky Publications Ltd. Reproduction without permission prohibited  Home\\u00bbSport\\u00bbParis Olympics 2024\\u00bbWhat time is Wayde van Niekerk in action on Wednesday night?  Wayde van Niekerk could be set for one of his final Olympic appearances on Wednesday night. Here is the exact time he's in action.  Wayde van Niekerk hasmanaged to reach the200m  semi-finals, but his third position in a pedestrian time of20.42during the Olympic heats failed to inspire hope of the 32-year-old being able to compete for a medal.  Nevertheless, there will still be plenty of attention on how he performs in Wednesday night's semi-final, in what could turn out to be his final Olympic appearance if he does not progress to the final.  The 200m semi-finals start at 20:02, with Shaun Maswanganyi also vying for a place in the final, while Van Niekerk will follow soon after at 20:18.  ATHLETICS  Men's 200m, semi-finals: (8.02pm):Shaun Maswanganyi  Men's 200m, semi-finals: (8.18pm):Wayde van Niekerk  Women's 400m, semi-finals: (9.01pm):Miranda Coetzee  DIVING  Women's 3m springboard prelims (3pm):Julia Vincent  Team SA sprinter Benjamin Richardson has beenwithdrawn from Paris 2024and will take no further part in these Olympics.  In confirming the news, the Team SA chief medical officer Dr Jean de Wilde said: \\\"Benjamin sustained a hamstring injury in the men's 200m heats on Monday and has been withdrawn from all further competition.\\\"  ATHLETICS  Women's 400m heats, repechage:Miranda Coetzee ran a PB (personal best) 50.66 to finish second in her heat and qualify for the semi-final  Men's 200m heats, repechage:Benjamin Richardson withdrawn  Men's 400m semi-finals :Lythe Pillay finished seventh in his semi-final in 45.24 and did not progress to the final  Men's 400m semi-finals:Zakhiti Nene finished sixth in his semi-final in 45.06 and did not progress to the final  Women's 400m hurdles, semi-finals:Zeney Geldenhuys ran a PB (personal best) 53.90 in her semi-final in finishing third which placed her 10th overall and just out the final  Women's 400m hurdles, semi-finals (8.17pm):Rogail Joseph ran a PB (personal best) 54.12 in her semi-final in finishing third which placed her 10th overall and just out the final  CANOEING  Men's kayak, double 500m heats:Hamish Lovemore and Andrew Birkett finished fourth behind Australians Jean van der Westhuyzen and Tom Green, and progressed to the quarter-finals  Men's kayak, double 500m quarter-finals:Hamish Lovemore and Andrew Birkett finished second behind the Spaniards Adrian Del Rio and Marcus Cooper and progressed to the semi-finals  Women's kayak, double 500m heats:Tiffany Koch and Esti Olivier finished fifth in their heat in 1:52.14 and progressed to the quarter-finals  Women's kayak, double 500m quarter-finals:Tiffany Koch and Esti Olivier finished sixth in their heat in 1:46.40 and were eliminated  SPORT CLIMBING  Women's boulder & Lead, semi-final boulder:Lauren Mukheibir placed 20th with 0.00  Men's speed, qualification:Joshua Bruyns finished 13th in the seeding qualification and went on to meet Amir Maimuratov of Kazakhstan in the heats. He was eliminated with a time of 5.84, with his opponent scoring 4.94  WIN R2 000: Take The South African's SASSA Survey  The South African is hiring! Freelance writing positions available  Follow The South African on Facebook for the latest local and international news  Follow The South African's WhatsApp channel for the latest sport, lifestyle and local news  Follow The South African on X for the latest, breaking news  A brand new shopping mall is coming to Pretoria East, bringing major retailers and new convenience to the area.  Orlando Pirates are reportedly set to welcome a new staff member in former Stellenbosch FC Head of Recruitment Brendon Fourie.  Masindi Nemtajela was stretched off during Orlando Pirates' 6-0 win over TS Galaxy on Sunday afternoon in Mbombela.  IT support is not just technical, it is personal.  Liema Pantsi's victory was clouded as fans of the 'Big Brother Mzansi' show expressed that Smash Afrika was unprofessional towards her.  A dominant weekend for the SA teams in the URC has made a big impact on the latest log standings as the playoffs edge closer.    TheSouthAfrican.com is all about South Africa and the stories that affect South Africans, wherever they are in the world.  We are independent.No agenda.No bias.  Our offices are for administrative purposes only, no visitors will be accepted without an appointment.  South Africa- Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd - Registration Number: 2005/028472/07 - Address: Regus Business Centre, 1st Floor, Block B, North Park, Black River Park, 2 Fir Street, Observatory, Cape Town, 7925, South Africa  Copyright Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd. All Rights Reserved.\"}"